node.text:
Here is an inspiring account of an individual who is adding to the story of a Better India. 
 
Despite resistance from his own community, Yasin Pathan, 70, has worked tirelessly all his life to preserve, renovate and restore 34 ancient Hindu temples around his village in West Bengal that had been lying in ruins and would perhaps have been lost without his efforts.
Pathan has received the Kabir award for his contribution to the cause of communal harmony.

node.text:
Picture 1 - An Architectural marvel - the Rani Ratnavati School

Situated in rural Jaisalmer , it is a symbiosis of modern design and ancient knowledge. Even in the scorching summers of Rajasthan the building maintains a cool temperature in the premises, through the designed airflow and ventilation system. A step towards eliminating the energy guzzling air conditioners and designing a more sustainable India. 

Picture 2 - Our Former president Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam – The missile man of India. 

A beacon in the advancement in areas from defence to Space research. Dr. Kalam embodies the nation's commitment towards society in the field of Science & Research to build a Better tomorrow.
